values:
So~ much to do after that long curse. Mm~, let me see...

Carmine, would you please take a look at the apartment next to ours and see if it is habitable, and if there is anything in particular it lacks?

Astaroth, Ion, I have good news &hearts; Abel and Esther are moving in next door to us~! Asta, we are to go furniture shopping with Esther &hearts;

<s>No news of Basil - though he is still safe and is returned to his proper place, it does not make the knowledge that we will likely never see him again any easier...</s>

<center><font size="5" color="pink">~&hearts; Is anyone looking for a job~? &hearts;~</font></center>

A bit of cooking and cleaning and running errands and so on~, being able to be discreet and not minding that the main working hours will be after sunset &hearts;

So~ many visitors &hearts; How lovely~.

..you wish to hug Ion~? Well, I don't see why not &hearts;

Would anyone like to have tea with me~?

Oh~, what lovely, <i>lovely</i> fireworks~! &hearts; 

Astaroth, Ion, we must~ go out and watch them, mm~? Especially since the City has seen fit to stop the sun from coming out today~!

Does anyone~ I know intend to join in the festivities~?

Oh~ dear, this was rather unexpected. It's rather strange to be so <i>tall</I> <s>and not female</s>.

I expect you have my body, Ingram~? Please do take care not to go out into the sun &hearts;

Speaking of which, it's been ages~ since I've been able to do so. I think I'll go for a walk~. Astaroth, Ion, I'll be out for a while &hearts;

I <i>do</i> hope everyone who was affected during the last curse is recovering well. Mm~, at least on the calmer days people seem to be rather festive~. There are one or two events planned, I heard~? &hearts;

<b>[Private to Household]</b>

I think~ it's about time we agree on a way to <i>deal</i> with these curses, especially the ones which affect the way we think. So far there's always been at least~ one of us who went unaffected. Who knows what could happen if we went wandering around while cursed, as happened to Shahrzad during the last one, hmm~?

So~, shall we reach an agreement on what those of us who go unaffected shall do during curses~? &hearts;

<s>Restraining and locking whoever is affected in their rooms sounds like a suitable option, in my opinion.</s>
